  <description type="morphology">Plants annual. Stems erect to ascending, branched, 4–6 dm, ± glandular-pubescent,
        white-villous. Leaves aromatic, distal leaves sessile; petiole 2–2.5 mm; blade lanceolate,
        2–9 × 0.5–4 cm, base cuneate, margins of distal leaves shallowly dentate to
        sinuate-pinnatifid, apex acuminate, villous and copiously gland-dotted (rarely nearly
        glabrous). Inflorescences terminal and axillary spikes, 3–15 cm; glomerules globose, 1.7–2.3
        mm diam.; bracts leaflike, narrowly ovate, 1–1.8 cm, apex acuminate. Flowers: perianth
        segments 5, connate for ca. 1/2 their length, distinct portion ovate, 0.7–1 mm, apex obtuse,
        rounded abaxially, villous, covering fruit at maturity; stamens 5; stigmas 3. Achenes ovoid;
        pericarp nonadherent, glandular. Seeds vertical, black, ovoid, 0.5–0.8 × 0.8 mm; seed coat
        smooth.</description>
